    "body": "### Problem\n\nNot sure if this is intended behaviour or a bug, but wanted to check. Say you have a 4-line block of code, starting from the first character on the top line, you press `<C-v>3jI>␣<C-o>` this already inserts the `>␣` at the start of each line, instead of keeping the future changes stashed until you finish editing the line (e.g. with `wi//<Esc>` or something). So essentially, are multi-line changes meant to be applied whenever you exit block-insert mode or only when you press Esc?\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSee problem",
